1 -> To copy a file from a remote to a local system, use the remote location as a source and local location as the destination:
scp remote_username@10.10.0.2:/remote/file.txt /local/directory
2 -> To copy a file from a local to a remote system run the following command:
scp file.txt remote_username@10.10.0.2:/remote/directory
3 -> To copy a directory from a local to remote system, use the -r option:
scp -r /local/directory remote_username@10.10.0.2:/remote/directory
